We have implemented spinal fusion patient dashboards using internal clinical and billing data and merged this data set with CMS raw historical and monthly claims data.  These data were central to redesigning transitional care pathways.  Stakeholders and care teams within the Spinal Fusion Episode of Care Team have implemented pathways to ensure more accurate and timely information around discharge, enabling the Transition of Care teams to plan for appropriate care needs post-discharge.

As anticipated we uncovered variations with patient education and care team discharge planning.  The creation of the Spinal Fusion Episode of Care team comprised of surgeons, MSHMC transitional care team, post-acute care admin, , nurses, social workers, and therapists has helped establish core principals to reduce variations across the two service lines that care for this patient population.  PSH and MSHMC have begun testing the impact of the multidisciplinary care protocols for all spinal fusion (non-cervical) patients and recently have seen changes in discharge disposition rates in performance period two.
